What the MD asked
"What would be your top three priorities to grow Open Banking adoption?"
He's not asking:
"How would you onboard?"
He's asking:
"What is your vision?"
A Strong Product Director Answer
Given your background, I'd answer:
My first priority would be increasing customer trust and transparency.
Open Banking only succeeds if customers understand the value exchange. I would focus on making consent, data usage, and customer controls simple and transparent so customers feel comfortable sharing data.
My second priority would be expanding the ecosystem of fintech and enterprise partners.
A platform becomes more valuable as more partners participate. I would identify high-value use cases and strategic partnerships that create meaningful customer experiences and drive adoption.
My third priority would be reducing friction for developers and partners.
Strong APIs, reliable onboarding, clear documentation, sandbox environments, and operational excellence are critical to scaling an Open Banking platform.
Ultimately, adoption is driven by three things: trust, ecosystem value, and ease of integration.
